proxmox-storage-migrate (1.2.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Docs only: README's Usage/Examples now show the installed command name
    (proxmox-storage-migrate) instead of bin/proxmox-storage-migrate; that
    path is only mentioned in the "From a checkout" section now, where it's
    actually relevant. No script changes.

 -- James Bolton <james@neojames.me>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 20:30:00 +0100

proxmox-storage-migrate (1.2.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix the apt repo: publish the package index under
    dists/stable/main/binary-amd64/ (was binary-all). A plain
    `deb [...] ... stable main` line — what install.sh/the README set up —
    only ever fetches binary-<native-arch>, so publishing solely under
    binary-all left `apt update`/`apt install`/`apt upgrade` unable to see
    any published version on a normal amd64 host (silently skipped with
    "doesn't support architecture 'amd64'"). No script changes.

 -- James Bolton <james@neojames.me>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 20:00:00 +0100

proxmox-storage-migrate (1.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * -s/-t are now required (from a flag or the config file below); they no
    longer default to empty and silently fail deep in storage.cfg lookup.
  * Add /etc/default/proxmox-storage-migrate: an optional config file
    setting new defaults for any flag. Command-line flags still override it.
  * Breaking: the installed command is now /usr/bin/proxmox-storage-migrate
    (was /usr/bin/migrate-disks), matching the package/repo name. The source
    script, man page, and per-run log directory prefix are renamed to match.
  * Shipped incrementally for testing as 1.2.0-beta.1 through 1.2.0-beta.4.

 -- James Bolton <james@neojames.me>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 19:30:00 +0100

